      "rationale": "SST k-omega selected following two-model sensitivity study (8.3% maximum NIH deviation vs. realizable k-epsilon). Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model applied; published correlation coefficients from Heuser and Opitz (1980) used. Model form uncertainty from turbulence closure is acknowledged as a residual limitation consistent with standard practice for MRL 2 assessments, though the specific magnitude of impact on worst-case identification has not been formally bounded. Gradation 2 considered achieved based on sensitivity study breadth."
